# Knowledge Base Directory

This directory will contain your converted AAOIFI standards in Markdown format.

## Automated Conversion (Recommended)

Use the AAOIFI converter script for automatic processing:

```bash
# 1. Place your PDFs in data/raw/aaoifi_standards/ with naming:
#    Standard_01_EN.pdf, Standard_01_AR.pdf, Standard_02_EN.pdf, etc.

# 2. Run the converter
python scripts/convert_aaoifi_to_markdown.py

# 3. Files will be automatically created here with comprehensive metadata
```

**Output format:**
```
AAOIFI_Standard_{number}_{lang}_{title}.md
```

**Examples:**
- `AAOIFI_Standard_01_en_Murabaha.md`
- `AAOIFI_Standard_01_ar_المرابحة.md`
- `AAOIFI_Standard_02_en_Ijarah_and_Ijarah_Muntahia_Bittamleek.md`

## Manual Conversion

### File Naming Convention

Use this pattern:
```
AAOIFI_[Standard-Type][Number]_[Topic-Keywords].md
```

### Examples

- `AAOIFI_FAS01_General-Presentation-and-Disclosure.md`
- `AAOIFI_FAS02_Murabaha-and-Murabaha-to-Purchase-Orderer.md`
- `AAOIFI_FAS03_Mudaraba-Financing.md`
- `AAOIFI_FAS21_Investment-in-Shares.md`

## How to Add Files

### Option 1: AAOIFI Converter (Recommended)
```bash
python scripts/convert_aaoifi_to_markdown.py
```
- Automatically extracts titles
- Generates comprehensive metadata
- Links bilingual pairs
- Creates INDEX.md

### Option 2: Generic PDF Converter
```bash
python scripts/convert_pdf_to_markdown.py --input-dir "path/to/pdfs/" --output-dir "."
```

### Option 3: Manual Addition
1. Convert your AAOIFI PDFs using online tools or manual extraction
2. Follow the naming convention above
3. Add YAML frontmatter with metadata
4. Upload all files to your Gemini Gem

## Metadata Structure

The AAOIFI converter automatically adds comprehensive metadata:

```yaml
---
document_type: "AAOIFI Shari'ah Standard"
standard_number: 1
title: "Murabaha"
language: "English"
language_code: "en"
source: "AAOIFI"
category: "Islamic Finance Standards"
subcategory: "Shari'ah Standards"
compliance_domain: "Islamic Banking and Finance"
topics:
  - Islamic Finance
  - Shari'ah Compliance
  - AAOIFI Standards
paired_document: "Standard_01_AR"
---
```

## Notes

- Keep each standard as one file unless it's over 100 pages
- Preserve section numbers (3.1, 3.2, etc.) for accurate citations
- Ensure text is clean and readable
- The AAOIFI converter handles bilingual pairing automatically
- Delete this .gitkeep file once you add your first standard
- An INDEX.md file will be auto-generated listing all standards
